<item>
            <title>[SPARK-26824] Streaming queries may store checkpoint data in a wrong directory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-26824</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When a user specifies a checkpoint location containing special chars that need to be escaped in a path, the streaming query will store checkpoint in a wrong place. For example, if you use &quot;/chk chk&quot;, the metadata will be stored in &quot;/chk%20chk&quot;. File sink&apos;s &quot;_spark_metadata&quot; directory has the same issue. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
